node.text:
To celebrate their 30th anniversary, @glsen partnered brilliant directors and other artists with students whose lives have been strongly and positively affected by this caring and crucial organization - and the caring and incredible people it attracts, people from all walks of life.

Together, these partnerships created short films that tell a story of change and growth and hope. This piece is about Gabriel and he was paired with director Joe Mantello. 

If you are able, join me in making a donation to @glsen so they may continue to ensure that schools, families, and peers respect and support LGBTQ+ students everywhere 💕

I love the “How I Spend My Sunday” features in the NYT; I found this one especially good, about Nicole Brienza, a nurse giving vaccine shots. Link in profile, but here’s an excerpt: 

In early January, Nicole Brienza, a recent nursing school graduate, was looking for work. When she found out about the huge vaccination program that was about to open at the Javits Center, she applied immediately. “Within an hour I got a call,” she said. Three days later she was offered a position there. “This job makes me feel like I’m part of history,” said Ms. Brienza, 24, whose first day at Javits was Jan. 17. “It’s a once-in-a-lifetime experience.” She lives with her parents, Carmela and Joe Brienza, and her younger brothers, Joey and Johnny, in Whitestone, Queens.

📸 by Karen Hagen

node.text: Here is a trailer for @specialnetflix the second and final season which, of course, is bittersweet - but mostly sweet. This is the first material Todd and I were interested in working on when the production company was just the two of us and no office or employees yet - and @ryanoconn still trusted us to do what we could to bring his story to life and OH MY GOD he blew our minds. We have been insanely fortunate to work with him and ALL of us are insanely fortunate to be able to enjoy what he’s created. Thank you @ryanoconn thank you @netflix and a huge thanks and congratulations to the many, many people who made major contributions to this project; you never forget your first. ❤️
